SPAIN DAYBOOK: Inditex Reports Earnings; Zapatero in Parliament

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-03-23T06:34:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/spain-daybook-inditex-reports-earnings-zapatero-in-parliament.html
Inditex SA (ITX) , the Spanish retailer
that owns the Zara and Massimo Dutti chains, reported full-year
net income climbed 32 percent to 1.73 billion euros ($2.45
billion).  Inditex holds a webcast conference call with analysts and
institutional investors at 9 a.m. CET. Chief Executive Officer
Pablo Isla will participate in a press conference at 11 a.m. in
Madrid, the company said in an e-mailed statement.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Prime Minister Jose Luis Rodriguez Zapatero and Finance
Minister Elena Salgado answer questions during a weekly session
in Parliament from 9 a.m. CET.  ECONOMY:
* Spain ’s National Statistics Institute reports February hotel
occupancy and prices.
*Spain’s Deputy Prime Minister Alfredo Perez Rubalcaba meets
with French Interior Minister Claude Gueant and will hold a
joint press conference at 8 p.m. in Madrid.
*Portugal’s government may collapse today as the country’s
parliament votes on budget cuts that have divided lawmakers,
JPMorgan economist Nicola Mai said.  EQUITIES:
* Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA (BBVA)  said in a filing it
completed its purchase of a 24.89 percent stake in Turkish
lender Turkiye Garanti Bankasi AS.
*Inditex reported full-year net profit rose 32 percent to 1.73
billion euros.
* Iberdrola SA (IBE)  said in a filing it boosted the maximum share
buyback to 4.30937 percent of its capital before its merging
with its renewable energy unit  Iberdrola Renovables SA. (IBR)  The
companies’ boards approved their merger plans. Renovables
commented in a regulatory filing.
* Mediaset SpA (MS) , the broadcaster owned by Italian Prime Minister
Silvio Berlusconi that controls  Gestevision Telecinco SA (TL5) , said
2010 profit rose 29 percent on higher advertising sales in Italy
and Spain. The board will propose a dividend of 35 cents per
share compared with 22 cents a share last year. Mediaset also
forecast an increase in net income this year.  MARKETS:
*The  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  advanced less than 0.1 percent to 10,576.1.
*The spread between Spanish and German 10-year borrowing costs
widened to 193.2.  -- Editor: Chris Peterson  To contact the reporter on this story:
